cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for constructing data-dependent kernels for semi-supervised learning, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The method is validated on both semi-supervised and unsupervised problems, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The method involves efficient computation of kernels, which may also be of interest to researchers in data structures (cs.DS) and neural networks (cs.NE).
